4513
4514struct isl_split_periods_data {
4515 int max_periods;
4516 isl_pw_qpolynomial *res;
4517};
4518
4519/* Create a slice where the integer division "div" has the fixed value "v".
4520 * In particular, if "div" refers to floor(f/m), then create a slice
4521 *
4522 * m v <= f <= m v + (m - 1)
4523 *
4524 * or
4525 *
4526 * f - m v >= 0
4527 * -f + m v + (m - 1) >= 0
4528 */
4529static __isl_give isl_set *set_div_slice(__isl_take isl_space *space,
4530 __isl_keep isl_qpolynomial *qp, int div, isl_int v)
4531{
4532 isl_size total;
4533 isl_basic_set *bset = NULL;
4534 int k;
4535
4536 total = isl_space_dim(space, isl_dim_all);
4537 if (total < 0 || !qp)
4538 goto error;
4539
4540 bset = isl_basic_set_alloc_space(isl_space_copy(space), 0, 0, 2);
4541
4542 k = isl_basic_set_alloc_inequality(bset);
4543 if (k < 0)
4544 goto error;
4545 isl_seq_cpy(bset->ineq[k], qp->div->row[div] + 1, 1 + total);
4546 isl_int_submul(bset->ineq[k][0], v, qp->div->row[div][0]);
4547
4548 k = isl_basic_set_alloc_inequality(bset);
4549 if (k < 0)
4550 goto error;
4551 isl_seq_neg(bset->ineq[k], qp->div->row[div] + 1, 1 + total);
4552 isl_int_addmul(bset->ineq[k][0], v, qp->div->row[div][0]);
4553 isl_int_add(bset->ineq[k][0], bset->ineq[k][0], qp->div->row[div][0]);
4554 isl_int_sub_ui(bset->ineq[k][0], bset->ineq[k][0], 1);
4555
4556 isl_space_free(space);
4557 return isl_set_from_basic_set(bset);
4558error:
4559 isl_basic_set_free(bset);
4560 isl_space_free(space);
4561 return NULL;
4562}
4563
4564static isl_stat split_periods(__isl_take isl_set *set,
4565 __isl_take isl_qpolynomial *qp, void *user);
4566
4567/* Create a slice of the domain "set" such that integer division "div"
4568 * has the fixed value "v" and add the results to data->res,
4569 * replacing the integer division by "v" in "qp".
4570 */
4571static isl_stat set_div(__isl_take isl_set *set,
4572 __isl_take isl_qpolynomial *qp, int div, isl_int v,
4573 struct isl_split_periods_data *data)
4574{
4575 int i;
4576 isl_size div_pos;
4577 isl_set *slice;
4578 isl_poly *cst;
4579
4580 slice = set_div_slice(isl_set_get_space(set), qp, div, v);
4581 set = isl_set_intersect(set, slice);
4582
4583 div_pos = isl_qpolynomial_domain_var_offset(qp, isl_dim_div);
4584 if (div_pos < 0)
4585 goto error;
4586
4587 for (i = div + 1; i < qp->div->n_row; ++i) {
4588 if (isl_int_is_zero(qp->div->row[i][2 + div_pos + div]))
4589 continue;
4590 isl_int_addmul(qp->div->row[i][1],
4591 qp->div->row[i][2 + div_pos + div], v);
4592 isl_int_set_si(qp->div->row[i][2 + div_pos + div], 0);
4593 }
4594
4595 cst = isl_poly_rat_cst(qp->dim->ctx, v, qp->dim->ctx->one);
4596 qp = substitute_div(qp, div, cst);
4597
4598 return split_periods(set, qp, data);
4599error:
4600 isl_set_free(set);
4601 isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
4602 return isl_stat_error;
4603}
4604
4605/* Split the domain "set" such that integer division "div"
4606 * has a fixed value (ranging from "min" to "max") on each slice
4607 * and add the results to data->res.
4608 */
4609static isl_stat split_div(__isl_take isl_set *set,
4610 __isl_take isl_qpolynomial *qp, int div, isl_int min, isl_int max,
4611 struct isl_split_periods_data *data)
4612{
4613 for (; isl_int_le(min, max); isl_int_add_ui(min, min, 1)) {
4614 isl_set *set_i = isl_set_copy(set);
4615 isl_qpolynomial *qp_i = isl_qpolynomial_copy(qp);
4616
4617 if (set_div(set_i, qp_i, div, min, data) < 0)
4618 goto error;
4619 }
4620 isl_set_free(set);
4621 isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
4622 return isl_stat_ok;
4623error:
4624 isl_set_free(set);
4625 isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
4626 return isl_stat_error;
4627}
4628
4629/* If "qp" refers to any integer division
4630 * that can only attain "max_periods" distinct values on "set"
4631 * then split the domain along those distinct values.
4632 * Add the results (or the original if no splitting occurs)
4633 * to data->res.
4634 */
4635static isl_stat split_periods(__isl_take isl_set *set,
4636 __isl_take isl_qpolynomial *qp, void *user)
4637{
4638 int i;
4639 isl_pw_qpolynomial *pwqp;
4640 struct isl_split_periods_data *data;
4641 isl_int min, max;
4642 isl_size div_pos;
4643 isl_stat r = isl_stat_ok;
4644
4645 data = (struct isl_split_periods_data *)user;
4646
4647 if (!set || !qp)
4648 goto error;
4649
4650 if (qp->div->n_row == 0) {
4651 pwqp = isl_pw_qpolynomial_alloc(set, qp);
4652 data->res = isl_pw_qpolynomial_add_disjoint(data->res, pwqp);
4653 return isl_stat_ok;
4654 }
4655
4656 div_pos = isl_qpolynomial_domain_var_offset(qp, isl_dim_div);
4657 if (div_pos < 0)
4658 goto error;
4659
4660 isl_int_init(min);
4661 isl_int_init(max);
4662 for (i = 0; i < qp->div->n_row; ++i) {
4663 enum isl_lp_result lp_res;
4664
4665 if (isl_seq_first_non_zero(qp->div->row[i] + 2 + div_pos,
4666 qp->div->n_row) != -1)
4667 continue;
4668
4669 lp_res = isl_set_solve_lp(set, 0, qp->div->row[i] + 1,
4670 set->ctx->one, &min, NULL, NULL);
4671 if (lp_res == isl_lp_error)
4672 goto error2;
4673 if (lp_res == isl_lp_unbounded || lp_res == isl_lp_empty)
4674 continue;
4675 isl_int_fdiv_q(min, min, qp->div->row[i][0]);
4676
4677 lp_res = isl_set_solve_lp(set, 1, qp->div->row[i] + 1,
4678 set->ctx->one, &max, NULL, NULL);
4679 if (lp_res == isl_lp_error)
4680 goto error2;
4681 if (lp_res == isl_lp_unbounded || lp_res == isl_lp_empty)
4682 continue;
4683 isl_int_fdiv_q(max, max, qp->div->row[i][0]);
4684
4685 isl_int_sub(max, max, min);
4686 if (isl_int_cmp_si(max, data->max_periods) < 0) {
4687 isl_int_add(max, max, min);
4688 break;
4689 }
4690 }
4691
4692 if (i < qp->div->n_row) {
4693 r = split_div(set, qp, i, min, max, data);
4694 } else {
4695 pwqp = isl_pw_qpolynomial_alloc(set, qp);
4696 data->res = isl_pw_qpolynomial_add_disjoint(data->res, pwqp);
4697 }
4698
4699 isl_int_clear(max);
4700 isl_int_clear(min);
4701
4702 return r;
4703error2:
4704 isl_int_clear(max);
4705 isl_int_clear(min);
4706error:
4707 isl_set_free(set);
4708 isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
4709 return isl_stat_error;
4710}

4712/* If any quasi-polynomial in pwqp refers to any integer division
4713 * that can only attain "max_periods" distinct values on its domain
4714 * then split the domain along those distinct values.
4715 */
4716__isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *isl_pw_qpolynomial_split_periods(
4717 __isl_take isl_pw_qpolynomial *pwqp, int max_periods)
4718{
4719 struct isl_split_periods_data data;
4720
4721 data.max_periods = max_periods;
4722 data.res = isl_pw_qpolynomial_zero(isl_pw_qpolynomial_get_space(pwqp));
4723
4724 if (isl_pw_qpolynomial_foreach_piece(pwqp, &split_periods, &data) < 0)
4725 goto error;
4726
4727 isl_pw_qpolynomial_free(pwqp);
4728
4729 return data.res;
4730error:
4731 isl_pw_qpolynomial_free(data.res);
4732 isl_pw_qpolynomial_free(pwqp);
4733 return NULL;
4734}

4736/* Construct a piecewise quasipolynomial that is constant on the given
4737 * domain. In particular, it is
4738 * 0 if cst == 0
4739 * 1 if cst == 1
4740 * infinity if cst == -1
4741 *
4742 * If cst == -1, then explicitly check whether the domain is empty and,
4743 * if so, return 0 instead.
4744 */
4745static __isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *constant_on_domain(
4746 __isl_take isl_basic_set *bset, int cst)
4747{
4748 isl_space *space;
4749 isl_qpolynomial *qp;
4750
4751 if (cst < 0 && isl_basic_set_is_empty(bset) == isl_bool_true)
4752 cst = 0;
4753 if (!bset)
4754 return NULL;
4755
4756 bset = isl_basic_set_params(bset);
4757 space = isl_basic_set_get_space(bset);
4758 if (cst < 0)
4759 qp = isl_qpolynomial_infty_on_domain(space);
4760 else if (cst == 0)
4761 qp = isl_qpolynomial_zero_on_domain(space);
4762 else
4763 qp = isl_qpolynomial_one_on_domain(space);
4764 return isl_pw_qpolynomial_alloc(isl_set_from_basic_set(bset), qp);
4765}

4767/* Internal data structure for multiplicative_call_factor_pw_qpolynomial.
4768 * "fn" is the function that is called on each factor.
4769 * "pwpq" collects the results.
4770 */
4771struct isl_multiplicative_call_data_pw_qpolynomial {
4772 __isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *(*fn)(__isl_take isl_basic_set *bset);
4773 isl_pw_qpolynomial *pwqp;
4774};

4776/* isl_factorizer_every_factor_basic_set callback that applies
4777 * data->fn to the factor "bset" and multiplies in the result
4778 * in data->pwqp.
4779 */
4780static isl_bool multiplicative_call_factor_pw_qpolynomial(
4781 __isl_keep isl_basic_set *bset, void *user)
4782{
4783 struct isl_multiplicative_call_data_pw_qpolynomial *data = user;
4784
4785 bset = isl_basic_set_copy(bset);
4786 data->pwqp = isl_pw_qpolynomial_mul(data->pwqp, data->fn(bset));
4787 if (!data->pwqp)
4788 return isl_bool_error;
4789
4790 return isl_bool_true;
4791}

4793/* Factor bset, call fn on each of the factors and return the product.
4794 *
4795 * If no factors can be found, simply call fn on the input.
4796 * Otherwise, construct the factors based on the factorizer,
4797 * call fn on each factor and compute the product.
4798 */
4799static __isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *compressed_multiplicative_call(
4800 __isl_take isl_basic_set *bset,
4801 __isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *(*fn)(__isl_take isl_basic_set *bset))
4802{
4803 struct isl_multiplicative_call_data_pw_qpolynomial data = { fn };
4804 isl_space *space;
4805 isl_set *set;
4806 isl_factorizer *f;
4807 isl_qpolynomial *qp;
4808 isl_bool every;
4809
4810 f = isl_basic_set_factorizer(bset);
4811 if (!f)
4812 goto error;
4813 if (f->n_group == 0) {
4814 isl_factorizer_free(f);
4815 return fn(bset);
4816 }
4817
4818 space = isl_basic_set_get_space(bset);
4819 space = isl_space_params(space);
4820 set = isl_set_universe(isl_space_copy(space));
4821 qp = isl_qpolynomial_one_on_domain(space);
4822 data.pwqp = isl_pw_qpolynomial_alloc(set, qp);
4823
4824 every = isl_factorizer_every_factor_basic_set(f,
4825 &multiplicative_call_factor_pw_qpolynomial, &data);
4826 if (every < 0)
4827 data.pwqp = isl_pw_qpolynomial_free(data.pwqp);
4828
4829 isl_basic_set_free(bset);
4830 isl_factorizer_free(f);
4831
4832 return data.pwqp;
4833error:
4834 isl_basic_set_free(bset);
4835 return NULL;
4836}

4838/* Factor bset, call fn on each of the factors and return the product.
4839 * The function is assumed to evaluate to zero on empty domains,
4840 * to one on zero-dimensional domains and to infinity on unbounded domains
4841 * and will not be called explicitly on zero-dimensional or unbounded domains.
4842 *
4843 * We first check for some special cases and remove all equalities.
4844 * Then we hand over control to compressed_multiplicative_call.
4845 */
4846__isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *isl_basic_set_multiplicative_call(
4847 __isl_take isl_basic_set *bset,
4848 __isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *(*fn)(__isl_take isl_basic_set *bset))
4849{
4850 isl_bool bounded;
4851 isl_size dim;
4852 isl_morph *morph;
4853 isl_pw_qpolynomial *pwqp;
4854
4855 if (!bset)
4856 return NULL;
4857
4858 if (isl_basic_set_plain_is_empty(bset))
4859 return constant_on_domain(bset, 0);
4860
4861 dim = isl_basic_set_dim(bset, isl_dim_set);
4862 if (dim < 0)
4863 goto error;
4864 if (dim == 0)
4865 return constant_on_domain(bset, 1);
4866
4867 bounded = isl_basic_set_is_bounded(bset);
4868 if (bounded < 0)
4869 goto error;
4870 if (!bounded)
4871 return constant_on_domain(bset, -1);
4872
4873 if (bset->n_eq == 0)
4874 return compressed_multiplicative_call(bset, fn);
4875
4876 morph = isl_basic_set_full_compression(bset);
4877 bset = isl_morph_basic_set(isl_morph_copy(morph), bset);
4878
4879 pwqp = compressed_multiplicative_call(bset, fn);
4880
4881 morph = isl_morph_dom_params(morph);
4882 morph = isl_morph_ran_params(morph);
4883 morph = isl_morph_inverse(morph);
4884
4885 pwqp = isl_pw_qpolynomial_morph_domain(pwqp, morph);
4886
4887 return pwqp;
4888error:
4889 isl_basic_set_free(bset);
4890 return NULL;
4891}

4893/* Drop all floors in "qp", turning each integer division [a/m] into
4894 * a rational division a/m. If "down" is set, then the integer division
4895 * is replaced by (a-(m-1))/m instead.
4896 */
4897static __isl_give isl_qpolynomial *qp_drop_floors(
4898 __isl_take isl_qpolynomial *qp, int down)
4899{
4900 int i;
4901 isl_poly *s;
4902
4903 if (!qp)
4904 return NULL;
4905 if (qp->div->n_row == 0)
4906 return qp;
4907
4908 qp = isl_qpolynomial_cow(qp);
4909 if (!qp)
4910 return NULL;
4911
4912 for (i = qp->div->n_row - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
4913 if (down) {
4914 isl_int_sub(qp->div->row[i][1],
4915 qp->div->row[i][1], qp->div->row[i][0]);
4916 isl_int_add_ui(qp->div->row[i][1],
4917 qp->div->row[i][1], 1);
4918 }
4919 s = isl_poly_from_affine(qp->dim->ctx, qp->div->row[i] + 1,
4920 qp->div->row[i][0], qp->div->n_col - 1);
4921 qp = substitute_div(qp, i, s);
4922 if (!qp)
4923 return NULL;
4924 }
4925
4926 return qp;
4927}
4928
4929/* Drop all floors in "pwqp", turning each integer division [a/m] into
4930 * a rational division a/m.
4931 */
4932static __isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *pwqp_drop_floors(
4933 __isl_take isl_pw_qpolynomial *pwqp)
4934{
4935 int i;
4936
4937 if (!pwqp)
4938 return NULL;
4939
4940 if (isl_pw_qpolynomial_is_zero(pwqp))
4941 return pwqp;
4942
4943 pwqp = isl_pw_qpolynomial_cow(pwqp);
4944 if (!pwqp)
4945 return NULL;
4946
4947 for (i = 0; i < pwqp->n; ++i) {
4948 pwqp->p[i].qp = qp_drop_floors(pwqp->p[i].qp, 0);
4949 if (!pwqp->p[i].qp)
4950 goto error;
4951 }
4952
4953 return pwqp;
4954error:
4955 isl_pw_qpolynomial_free(pwqp);
4956 return NULL;
4957}

4959/* Adjust all the integer divisions in "qp" such that they are at least
4960 * one over the given orthant (identified by "signs"). This ensures
4961 * that they will still be non-negative even after subtracting (m-1)/m.
4962 *
4963 * In particular, f is replaced by f' + v, changing f = [a/m]
4964 * to f' = [(a - m v)/m].
4965 * If the constant term k in a is smaller than m,
4966 * the constant term of v is set to floor(k/m) - 1.
4967 * For any other term, if the coefficient c and the variable x have
4968 * the same sign, then no changes are needed.
4969 * Otherwise, if the variable is positive (and c is negative),
4970 * then the coefficient of x in v is set to floor(c/m).
4971 * If the variable is negative (and c is positive),
4972 * then the coefficient of x in v is set to ceil(c/m).
4973 */
4974static __isl_give isl_qpolynomial *make_divs_pos(__isl_take isl_qpolynomial *qp,
4975 int *signs)
4976{
4977 int i, j;
4978 isl_size div_pos;
4979 isl_vec *v = NULL;
4980 isl_poly *s;
4981
4982 qp = isl_qpolynomial_cow(qp);
4983 div_pos = isl_qpolynomial_domain_var_offset(qp, isl_dim_div);
4984 if (div_pos < 0)
4985 return isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
4986 qp->div = isl_mat_cow(qp->div);
4987 if (!qp->div)
4988 goto error;
4989
4990 v = isl_vec_alloc(qp->div->ctx, qp->div->n_col - 1);
4991
4992 for (i = 0; i < qp->div->n_row; ++i) {
4993 isl_int *row = qp->div->row[i];
4994 v = isl_vec_clr(v);
4995 if (!v)
4996 goto error;
4997 if (isl_int_lt(row[1], row[0])) {
4998 isl_int_fdiv_q(v->el[0], row[1], row[0]);
4999 isl_int_sub_ui(v->el[0], v->el[0], 1);
5000 isl_int_submul(row[1], row[0], v->el[0]);
5001 }
5002 for (j = 0; j < div_pos; ++j) {
5003 if (isl_int_sgn(row[2 + j]) * signs[j] >= 0)
5004 continue;
5005 if (signs[j] < 0)
5006 isl_int_cdiv_q(v->el[1 + j], row[2 + j], row[0]);
5007 else
5008 isl_int_fdiv_q(v->el[1 + j], row[2 + j], row[0]);
5009 isl_int_submul(row[2 + j], row[0], v->el[1 + j]);
5010 }
5011 for (j = 0; j < i; ++j) {
5012 if (isl_int_sgn(row[2 + div_pos + j]) >= 0)
5013 continue;
5014 isl_int_fdiv_q(v->el[1 + div_pos + j],
5015 row[2 + div_pos + j], row[0]);
5016 isl_int_submul(row[2 + div_pos + j],
5017 row[0], v->el[1 + div_pos + j]);
5018 }
5019 for (j = i + 1; j < qp->div->n_row; ++j) {
5020 if (isl_int_is_zero(qp->div->row[j][2 + div_pos + i]))
5021 continue;
5022 isl_seq_combine(qp->div->row[j] + 1,
5023 qp->div->ctx->one, qp->div->row[j] + 1,
5024 qp->div->row[j][2 + div_pos + i], v->el,
5025 v->size);
5026 }
5027 isl_int_set_si(v->el[1 + div_pos + i], 1);
5028 s = isl_poly_from_affine(qp->dim->ctx, v->el,
5029 qp->div->ctx->one, v->size);
5030 qp->poly = isl_poly_subs(qp->poly, div_pos + i, 1, &s);
5031 isl_poly_free(s);
5032 if (!qp->poly)
5033 goto error;
5034 }
5035
5036 isl_vec_free(v);
5037 return qp;
5038error:
5039 isl_vec_free(v);
5040 isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
5041 return NULL;
5042}

5044struct isl_to_poly_data {
5045 int sign;
5046 isl_pw_qpolynomial *res;
5047 isl_qpolynomial *qp;
5048};
5049
5050/* Appoximate data->qp by a polynomial on the orthant identified by "signs".
5051 * We first make all integer divisions positive and then split the
5052 * quasipolynomials into terms with sign data->sign (the direction
5053 * of the requested approximation) and terms with the opposite sign.
5054 * In the first set of terms, each integer division [a/m] is
5055 * overapproximated by a/m, while in the second it is underapproximated
5056 * by (a-(m-1))/m.
5057 */
5058static isl_stat to_polynomial_on_orthant(__isl_take isl_set *orthant,
5059 int *signs, void *user)
5060{
5061 struct isl_to_poly_data *data = user;
5062 isl_pw_qpolynomial *t;
5063 isl_qpolynomial *qp, *up, *down;
5064
5065 qp = isl_qpolynomial_copy(data->qp);
5066 qp = make_divs_pos(qp, signs);
5067
5068 up = isl_qpolynomial_terms_of_sign(qp, signs, data->sign);
5069 up = qp_drop_floors(up, 0);
5070 down = isl_qpolynomial_terms_of_sign(qp, signs, -data->sign);
5071 down = qp_drop_floors(down, 1);
5072
5073 isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
5074 qp = isl_qpolynomial_add(up, down);
5075
5076 t = isl_pw_qpolynomial_alloc(orthant, qp);
5077 data->res = isl_pw_qpolynomial_add_disjoint(data->res, t);
5078
5079 return isl_stat_ok;
5080}
5081
5082/* Approximate each quasipolynomial by a polynomial. If "sign" is positive,
5083 * the polynomial will be an overapproximation. If "sign" is negative,
5084 * it will be an underapproximation. If "sign" is zero, the approximation
5085 * will lie somewhere in between.
5086 *
5087 * In particular, is sign == 0, we simply drop the floors, turning
5088 * the integer divisions into rational divisions.
5089 * Otherwise, we split the domains into orthants, make all integer divisions
5090 * positive and then approximate each [a/m] by either a/m or (a-(m-1))/m,
5091 * depending on the requested sign and the sign of the term in which
5092 * the integer division appears.
5093 */
5094__isl_give isl_pw_qpolynomial *isl_pw_qpolynomial_to_polynomial(
5095 __isl_take isl_pw_qpolynomial *pwqp, int sign)
5096{
5097 int i;
5098 struct isl_to_poly_data data;
5099
5100 if (sign == 0)
5101 return pwqp_drop_floors(pwqp);
5102
5103 if (!pwqp)
5104 return NULL;
5105
5106 data.sign = sign;
5107 data.res = isl_pw_qpolynomial_zero(isl_pw_qpolynomial_get_space(pwqp));
5108
5109 for (i = 0; i < pwqp->n; ++i) {
5110 if (pwqp->p[i].qp->div->n_row == 0) {
5111 isl_pw_qpolynomial *t;
5112 t = isl_pw_qpolynomial_alloc(
5113 isl_set_copy(pwqp->p[i].set),
5114 isl_qpolynomial_copy(pwqp->p[i].qp));
5115 data.res = isl_pw_qpolynomial_add_disjoint(data.res, t);
5116 continue;
5117 }
5118 data.qp = pwqp->p[i].qp;
5119 if (isl_set_foreach_orthant(pwqp->p[i].set,
5120 &to_polynomial_on_orthant, &data) < 0)
5121 goto error;
5122 }
5123
5124 isl_pw_qpolynomial_free(pwqp);
5125
5126 return data.res;
5127error:
5128 isl_pw_qpolynomial_free(pwqp);
5129 isl_pw_qpolynomial_free(data.res);
5130 return NULL;
5131}

5134 __isl_take isl_pw_qpolynomial *pwqp, void *user)
5135{
5136 int *sign = user;

5138 return isl_pw_qpolynomial_to_polynomial(pwqp, *sign);

5148__isl_give isl_basic_map *isl_basic_map_from_qpolynomial(
5149 __isl_take isl_qpolynomial *qp)
5150{
5151 int i, k;
5152 isl_space *space;
5153 isl_vec *aff = NULL;
5154 isl_basic_map *bmap = NULL;
5155 isl_bool is_affine;
5156 unsigned pos;
5157 unsigned n_div;
5158
5159 if (!qp)
5160 return NULL;
5161 is_affine = isl_poly_is_affine(qp->poly);
5162 if (is_affine < 0)
5163 goto error;
5164 if (!is_affine)
5165 isl_die(qp->dim->ctx, isl_error_invalid,
5166 "input quasi-polynomial not affine", goto error);
5167 aff = isl_qpolynomial_extract_affine(qp);
5168 if (!aff)
5169 goto error;
5170 space = isl_qpolynomial_get_space(qp);
5171 pos = 1 + isl_space_offset(space, isl_dim_out);
5172 n_div = qp->div->n_row;
5173 bmap = isl_basic_map_alloc_space(space, n_div, 1, 2 * n_div);
5174
5175 for (i = 0; i < n_div; ++i) {
5176 k = isl_basic_map_alloc_div(bmap);
5177 if (k < 0)
5178 goto error;
5179 isl_seq_cpy(bmap->div[k], qp->div->row[i], qp->div->n_col);
5180 isl_int_set_si(bmap->div[k][qp->div->n_col], 0);
5181 bmap = isl_basic_map_add_div_constraints(bmap, k);
5182 }
5183 k = isl_basic_map_alloc_equality(bmap);
5184 if (k < 0)
5185 goto error;
5186 isl_int_neg(bmap->eq[k][pos], aff->el[0]);
5187 isl_seq_cpy(bmap->eq[k], aff->el + 1, pos);
5188 isl_seq_cpy(bmap->eq[k] + pos + 1, aff->el + 1 + pos, n_div);
5189
5190 isl_vec_free(aff);
5191 isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
5192 bmap = isl_basic_map_finalize(bmap);
5193 return bmap;
5194error:
5195 isl_vec_free(aff);
5196 isl_qpolynomial_free(qp);
5197 isl_basic_map_free(bmap);
5198 return NULL;
5199}
